name: GlobalPayroll-PayGroups-GET-getPeriods
description: [Global Payroll] GET /payGroups/{ID}/periods — Retrieves a collection of payroll periods for the specified Payroll Interface pay group ID.

schema.name: ID
schema.description: The Workday ID of the resource.

schema.name: limit
schema.description: The maximum number of objects in a single response. The default is 20. The maximum is 100.

schema.name: offset
schema.description: The zero-based index of the first object in a response collection. The default is 0. Use offset with the limit parameter to control paging of a response collection. Example: If limit is 5 and offset is 9, the response returns a collection of 5 objects starting with the 10th object.

schema.name: periodEndDate
schema.description: The end date of a payroll period using the yyyy-mm-dd format. This should not be used with the showMostRecentOnly query parameter. If both periodEndDate and showMostRecentOnly query parameters are provided, the API will only consider the periodEndDate query parameter.

schema.name: showMostRecentOnly
schema.description: If true, the operation returns the 5 most recent pay periods. This should not be used with periodEndDate query parameter. If both showMostRecentOnly and periodEndDate query parameters are provided, the API will ignore showMostRecentOnly query parameter.
